                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/5467.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul at Chihuahua</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Chihuahua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-11-11T12:00:00-07:04">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 11, 1912—12 noon</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Rebels have about 300 near railroad 50 miles north and about 200 in two or three
                    detachments in western part of State.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Letcher.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
